@{b}@{u}

Introduction@{uu}@{ub}

FileMaster is copyright ©1992-1995 by Toni Wilen, all rights reserved.
Now it is Released under GPL.
Since 3.1 Beta 5 i, Christian Kummerow bugfix and Enhance FM for the 68k.
I quick rewrote this guide, please note it may not uptodate - use the
Readme.



@{b}@{u}Distribution@{ub}@{uu}

Filemaster is now released under GPL. 

@{b}@{u}Information about long-awaited FileMaster 3.2@{ub}@{uu}

New features:

    - Multitasking. You can for example format, copy and view pictures
      at the same time.
    - @{"Screen size&mode" link CON_Screen} requester
    - User selectable fonts for text, directory window and text viewer.
    - @{"Window size" link CON_Screen} gadget. Useful if FileMaster is opened on Workbench
      or public screen.
    - 1-8 directory windows simultaneously on screen.
    - Full @{"keyboard support." link Keyboardsupport}
    - JPEG image viewer built in Kickstart 3.0/68020 -version.
    - @{"ShowPic" link CMD_ShowPic}/@{"Show Asc/Hex" link CMD_ShowASC} and @{"Hear" link CMD_Hear} have buffered input.
    - Localizable
    - AGA support

New features/features missing or incomplete, but will be implemented later:

    - Own Intuition window for every directory list window


FileMaster 3.2 comes in two versions:
One for 68000 and one for 68020 or higher, for now both require Kickstart 3.0
I hope in 2007 all users have that


@ENDNODE
