@{u}@{b}Sleep@{uu}@{ub}

    Iconifies FileMastes
    -
    @{b}Sleep window@{ub}    Open sleep window with available memory
            and current time (If Workbench is unavailable
            sleep window is always opened)

@ENDNODE
@NODE CMD_S->D "FileMaster 3.1: S->D"

@{u}@{b}S->D@{uu}@{ub}

    Copies source window in to destination window

@ENDNODE
@NODE CMD_Drives "FileMaster 3.1: Drives"

@{u}@{b}Drives@{uu}@{ub}

    Lists all volumes, devices and assigns on source window.

@ENDNODE
@NODE CMD_Parent "FileMaster 3.1: Parent"

@{u}@{b}Parent@{uu}@{ub}

    Goes source window's parent directory
    -
    @{b}Directory buffers@{ub}    number of fast-parent buffers.

@ENDNODE
@NODE CMD_Invert "FileMaster 3.1: Invert"

@{u}@{b}Invert@{uu}@{ub}

    Clears all selected files/directories and selects all unselected
    files/directories on source window.

@ENDNODE
@NODE CMD_Clear "FileMaster 3.1: Clear"

@{u}@{b}Clear@{uu}@{ub}

    Clears all selected files/directories on source window.

@ENDNODE
@NODE CMD_Operate "FileMaster 3.1: Operate"

@{u}@{b}Operate@{uu}@{ub}

    Combined rename, set protection, date  and change comment -command.
    Requester opens with gadgets for directory name, comment, date and
    protection flags. With All-gadget you can change protection
    flags, comments or dates for all selected files or directories.

@ENDNODE
@NODE CMD_Copy "FileMaster 3.1: Copy"

@{u}@{b}Copy@{uu}@{ub}

    Copies selected files/directories to destination directory.
    Directories which contains directories/files are also copied.
    -
    @{b}Refresh@{ub}            Selects update method for destination
                (full/partial/until end)
    @{b}Overwrite@{ub}        (always/ask)
    @{b}Clone comment@{ub}        (yes/no)
    @{b}Clone flags@{ub}        (yes/no)
    @{b}Clone date@{ub}        (yes/no)
    @{b}Check free space@{ub}    Checks if destination has enough free space
    @{b}Maximum buffer size@{ub}    Maximum size of copy buffer

@ENDNODE
@NODE CMD_CopyAs "FileMaster 3.1: Copy As"

@{u}@{b}Copy As@{uu}@{ub}

    Same as copy, but asks for destination name.
    -
    @{b}Refresh@{ub}            Selects update method for destination
                (full/partial/until end)
    @{b}Overwrite@{ub}        (always/ask)
    @{b}Clone comment@{ub}        (yes/no)
    @{b}Clone flags@{ub}        (yes/no)
    @{b}Clone date@{ub}        (yes/no)
    @{b}Check free space@{ub}    Checks if destination has enough free space
    @{b}Maximum buffer size@{ub}    Maximum size of copy buffer

@ENDNODE
@NODE CMD_Move "FileMaster 3.1: Move"

@{u}@{b}Move@{uu}@{ub}

    Moves files and directories
    If source and destination are on the same device Move uses
    Rename(), but if they aren't Copy and Delete commands are used.
    Config is used only if copying+deleting is needed. Rename()
    automatically keeps comment and protection flags.
    -
    @{b}Refresh@{ub}            Selects update method for destination
                and source
                (full/partial/until end)
    @{b}Overwrite@{ub}        (always/ask)
    @{b}Clone comment@{ub}        (yes/no)
    @{b}Clone flags@{ub}        (yes/no)
    @{b}Clone date@{ub}        (yes/no)
    @{b}Check free space@{ub}    Checks if destination has enough free space
    @{b}Maximum buffer size@{ub}    Maximum size of copy buffer

@ENDNODE
@NODE CMD_Delete "FileMaster 3.1: Delete"

@{u}@{b}Delete@{uu}@{ub}

    Deletes files and directories
    Directories which contains directories/files are also deleted.
    -
    @{b}Refresh@{ub}            Selects update method for source
                (full/partial/until end)
    @{b}Confirm deletion confirms before deleting anything
    Confirm deletion of non-empty subdirecotries
    Confirm deletion of protected files and dirs@{ub}

@ENDNODE
@NODE CMD_MakeDir "FileMaster 3.1: Make directory"

@{u}@{b}MakeDir@{uu}@{ub}

    Create directory
    Requester opens with gadgets for directory name, comment, date
    and protection flags.

@ENDNODE
@NODE CMD_ShowAsc "FileMaster 3.1: Show ASCII / HEX"

@{u}@{b}Show Asc/Show Hex@{uu}@{ub}

    Shows files as text or in hexadecimal
    Plain/bold-face/italic/underscore and inverse video,
    foreground and background color control sequences supported.

    @{b}cursor up/keypad 8@{ub}    fast scroll down
    @{b}cursor down/keypad 2@{ub}    fast scroll up
    @{b}cursor left/keypad 4@{ub}    smooth scroll up
    @{b}cursor right/keypad 6@{ub}    smooth scroll down
    @{b}keypad 7@{ub}        top of text
    @{b}keypad 1@{ub}        end of text
    @{b}keypad 9@{ub}        page up
    @{b}keypad 3@{ub}        page down
    @{b}J@{ub}            jump to line
    @{b}S@{ub}            string search requester
    @{b}R-Amiga + S@{ub}        search
    @{b}left mousebutton/<ESC>@{ub}    exit
    @{b}mouse pointer on top@{ub}    fast scroll up
    @{b}of screen@{ub}
    @{b}mouse pointer on bottom@{ub}    fast scroll down
    @{b}of screen@{ub}
    -
    @{b}Infoline always@{ub}        show infoline always on bottom of screen
                turn this off if scrolling isn't smooth

@ENDNODE
@NODE CMD_ShowPic "FileMaster 3.1: Show picture"

@{u}@{b}Show Pic@{uu}@{ub}

    Shows IFF pictures, Workbench icons, fonts and colorfonts
    While viewing icons or fonts press keys 1-8 to change screen depth.
    Kickstart 3.0/68020 CPU version of FileMaster 3.0 can also
    show JPEG pictures. JPEG's are shown in HAM8 on AGA and in
    16 color grayscale on ECS/OCS chipset.
    JPEG code is based on Independent JPEG Group's C-sources.

    left mousebutton/<ESC>/<Return> exits

    Pictures can too shown via Datatypes.


    3.2B1:
     New Options:

    @{b}Show Pictures on FM Screen@{ub} - does that like it sounds. FM need to run in >8Bit Depth
 
    @{b}Resize Big Pictures@{ub} - if the pic is to big to fit on the fm screen ShowPic scale it

    @{b}Resize Small Pictures@{ub} if the pic is smaller than fm screensize it gets upscaled

    If you decide that Big Pictures get not Resized you can scrool in the Picture via Cursor Keys.


@ENDNODE
@NODE CMD_PlayMod "FileMaster 3.1: Play module"

@{u}@{b}Play Mod@{uu}@{ub}

    Plays normal 32-sample ProTracker modules
    Right mousebutton click on the bottom of the FileMaster's screen
    stops playing.
    Key between ESC and TAB fast forwards

@ENDNODE
@NODE CMD_DiskInfo "FileMaster 3.1: Disk info"

@{u}@{b}DiskInfo@{uu}@{ub}

    Shows technical information about real disks

@ENDNODE
@NODE CMD_Execute "FileMaster 3.1: Execute"

@{u}@{b}Execute@{uu}@{ub}

    Runs executables

    t: must be assigned somewhere (preferably to ram disk) for
    Execute to work

    -
    @{b}Window@{ub}         window parameter for NewCLI.

@ENDNODE
@NODE CMD_DiskSize "FileMaster 3.1: Disk Size"

@{u}@{b}DiskSize@{uu}@{ub}

    Calculates the size of the contents of selected directory/ies.
    Shows size in bytes, and number of files and directories.
    Calculates all sub-directories as well.

@ENDNODE
@NODE CMD_ModInfo "FileMaster 3.1: Module Info"

@{u}@{b}ModInfo@{uu}@{ub}

    Shows information about currently playing module

@ENDNODE
@NODE CMD_Hear "FileMaster 3.2: Hear"

@{u}@{b}Hear@{uu}@{ub}

    Plays RAW, IFF-8SVX, CDDA(Motorola Format) and mp3´s via mpega.library
    -
    @{b}Ask frequency@{ub}    Asks new frequency always

    @{b}Play from@{ub}        Disk=read from disk and play at the same time
                     Memory=reads sample in to memory before playing
                     Ask=asks play mode before playing
                     If not enough Chipmem for the Sample is available it reads from Disk
                     and ignore this setting.

    @{b}Default freq@{ub}     Default frequency for non IFF samples

    @{b}Buffer size@{ub}      Size of playing buffers. (two Chipmem buffers are allocated)

    @{b}Audio Filter off for >10khz@{ub} switch off the Audio Filter for Samples over 10khz

    @{b}Downscale CDDA to 22050@{ub} if you use PAL Screens max.28khz playback is possible,
                            FM downsample it to hear it in the right speed. 

    @{b}MP3 frequency divisior@{ub}  div the mp3 frequency for playback with PAL or speedup the
                            decoding if you have a Low End Amiga  

    @{b}MP3 Quality@{ub}      set the decoding quality for mp3, on Low End Amiga you may have set
                     to med or low.


For CDDA playback a extra Buffer, 2 times or 4 times(Downsample) Buffersize of Fastmem is
additional allocated.
The Recommend buffer size for CDDA and stereo playback in Multitasking is >=80000kb because
the Buffer must be shared between 2 Channels.
For MP3 playback a extra Buffer, 2 times Buffersize of Fastmem is additional allocated.

MP3 settings:
For 68060 44100/Stereo/HighQual and other cpu intensiv applications running at the same time a
Buffer value of 122880 is recommend,at 22050/Stereo/HighQual the default value of 80000 is enough.

The 68030@50MHZ can only handle 1/4 freq/Stereo/LowQual and require a Buffersize of 160000 Bytes.

Make sure that you use the mpega.library from Stephane TAVENARD, i tryed other Versions all
are slower.
Usual the FPU Versions of programs are faster, but with mpga this is the opposite, if you want
more speed use the non FPU Version.

@ENDNODE
@NODE CMD_FileEdit "FileMaster 3.1: FileEdit"

@{u}@{b}FileEdit@{uu}@{ub}

    Edit files in ascii or hex

    mouse with left button pressed turns editing mode on and moves
    cursor, right button turns editing mode off.

    When editing mode is on:

    @{b}cursor up/keypad 8@{ub}        move cursor one line up.
    @{b}cursor down/keypad 2@{ub}        move cursor one line down.
    @{b}cursor left/keypad 4@{ub}        move cursor one character left.
    @{b}cursor right/keypad 6@{ub}        move cursor one character right.

    When editing mode is off:

    @{b}cursor up/keypad 9@{ub}        previous page
    @{b}cursor down/keypad 3@{ub}        next page
    @{b}cursor left/keypad 8@{ub}        scroll one line up
    @{b}cursor right/keypad 2@{ub}        scroll one line down
    @{b}keypad 7@{ub}            move to start of file
    @{b}keypad 1@{ub}            move to end of file

    Gadgets on bottom of screen:

    @{b}Find@{ub}    Searchs for text or hexadecimal string, key shortcut 'f'
        Right Amiga + 'f' continues searching
        Following search modes are possible:

        1. String search
            The first character must be something else
            than a '$'. No case dependecy. Max. 32 characters
            Example: "find me"

        2. Hex search
            First character must be '$'
            Max. 31 characters (15 bytes)
            Example: "$03d27f"

    @{b}Undo@{ub}    Undoes changes in editing area. Key 'u'
        (Scrolling up/down also undoes all changes)

    @{b}Write@{ub}    Writes changes to disk. You can't undo this. Key 'w'

    @{b}Exit@{ub}    Exits FileEdit. Key 'e'
        
    NOTE:    Key shortcuts can not be changed and text fore/background
        is same as on FileEdit's gadget label

@ENDNODE
@NODE CMD_DiskEdit "FileMaster 3.1: DiskEdit"

@{u}@{b}DiskEdit@{uu}@{ub}

    Edit track supporting devices directly.

    ************************ WARNING *************************

    Don't use DiskEdit, if you don't know what you are doing!!
    You can destroy your files, if used incorrectly!!!
    Additonal: i think there is a 2 GB limit for using it!

    **********************************************************

    DiskEdit goes directly to root block or to file/directory header
    block if disk is dos-disk and you have selected directory or file
    from directory list.

    mouse with left button pressed turns editing mode on and moves
    cursor, right button turns editing mode off.

    When editing mode is on:

    @{b}cursor up/keypad 8@{ub}        move cursor one line up.
    @{b}cursor down/keypad 2@{ub}        move cursor one line down.
    @{b}cursor left/keypad 4@{ub}        move cursor one character left.
    @{b}cursor right/keypad 6@{ub}        move cursor one character right.

    When editing mode is off:

    @{b}cursor up&left/keypad 8@{ub}    previous block
    @{b}cursor down&right/keypad 2@{ub}    next block
    @{b}keypad 7@{ub}            first block (0)
    @{b}keypad 1@{ub}            last block (depends on device)
    @{b}keypad 9@{ub}            page up if screen size is
                        smaller than blocksize
    @{b}keypad 3@{ub}            page down if screen size is
                        smaller than blocksize

    @{b}B@{ub}                next block
    @{b}T@{ub}                next track
    @{b}S@{ub}                next sector
    @{b}H@{ub}                next head
    @{b}SHIFT + B@{ub}            previous block
    @{b}SHIFT + T@{ub}            previous track
    @{b}SHIFT + S@{ub}            previous sector
    @{b}SHIFT + H@{ub}            previous head

    Gadgets between edit windows and message window:

    window with the device        root block
    name on it

    string gadgets next to        enter position directly
    B/T/S/H -characters

    B/T/S/H    -characters        left mousebutton adds and
                    right mousebutton subracts
                    value next to it by 1

    Gadgets on bottom of screen:

    @{b}Find@{ub}    Searches for text or hexadecimal string, key shortcut 'f'
        Right Amiga + 'f' continues searching
        Following search modes are possible:

        1. String search
            The first character must be something else
            than a '$'. No case dependecy. Max. 32 characters
            Example: "find me"

        2. Hex search
            First character must be '$'
            Max. 31 characters (15 bytes)
            Example: "$03d27f"

    @{b}Undo@{ub}    Undoes changes in editing area. Key 'u'

    @{b}Write@{ub}    Writes changes to disk. You can't undo this. Key 'w'
            Asks if you want to fix checksum (only if
            checksum isn't already correct)

    @{b}Exit@{ub}    Exits DiskEdit. Key 'e'

    NOTE:    Key shortcuts can not be changed and text
        fore/background is same as on DiskEdit's gadget label

    -

    @{b}Ignore LowCyl@{ub}    If selected DiskEdit ignores de_LowCyl from
            disk environment array. Note: DiskEdit doesn't
            find root block or file/dir headers correctly
            when this is selected! Useful for examining
            harddisks' RDSK-blocks.

@ENDNODE
@NODE CMD_About "FileMaster 3.1: About"

@{u}@{b}About@{uu}@{ub}

    Shows the user's name if registered and author's address.

@ENDNODE
@NODE CMD_Register "FileMaster 3.1: Register"

@{u}@{b}Register@{uu}@{ub}

    Writes the registeration form to file or to printer.

@ENDNODE
@NODE CMD_Compare "FileMaster 3.1 B11: Compare"

@{u}@{b}Compare@{uu}@{ub}

    Compare Selected Source Files Byte by Byte with Destination Files


Requirement: 256kb Freemem and enough space in t: for a DVD-DL this can easy be 10 MB


For example for Verify a DVD Backup or Look for changed Files.

I wrote this because cmp.020 by ALeX Kazik is good but really slow and integrating this into
FM gui make the use easier.
This funktion is about 36-49% faster then cmp.020
Everytime all Files compared byte by byte if the size is equal, don`t care about
filedates.


Black means the source file has the same contains like the destfile
Italic black means file not found or file can`t opened
White means the source size is another than the destination size
Blue means the containt of the files is different.

The result is shown with the FM ShowASC Command and saved in T:FMCompare.txt

No Speacial settings.




@ENDNODE


@NODE CMD_DoubDelete "FileMaster 3.1 B12: Double Delete"

 Delete Double Files in a Volume or a Dir


Requirement: Dupefinder by Kjell Irgens
http://aminet.net/util/cli/DupeFinder12.lha in C: or a Path.


Dupefinder is a good and fast tool, it outputs you double Files in a CLI.

But its slow to go through the List and then locate the double files with Workbench,
Filemaster or typing Delete and copy&paste the Path.
I decide to use Filemaster for that.
Filemaster now runs dupefinder with the selected Volume/Dir and waits for finish.
Now Filemaster extract the Information from the List and open a Window for each
double File. In that Window you can choice the File of the doubles to delete(A B C), or none.

Maximum double files recognized is Limitet to 3. If there are more you have to
run DoubDelete again. More than 3 Doubles are shown with Points.

Dupefinder is runned with NOICONS and MINSIZE=10, to avoid icons and Envoirement Settings Files.


No Spechial settings.



@ENDNODE


@NODE CMD_Volume "FileMaster 3.1 B12: Volume"
The Volume Command allows you to Put Drives in the Gadget Bar.

Copy Volume to Gadget Bar and change the Label to your drive, for example SYS:

If you click now on that Button the Drive is read in the actual List.


@ENDNODE

@NODE CMD_Find "FileMaster 3.2 Beta 2: Find"


Search in the selected items for Files that match the given Filename or/and the given Contains.
For Filename you can enter a part of the Filename, too you can use #? patterns.

The search is case insensitiv.

The Results are shown in the Filemaster list, its limited to 108 chars depth.
You can click on the files for view/operate/delete them but copy or move operations are not possible

@ENDNODE




