@NODE CON_Screen "FileMaster 3.1: Screen / Layout Configuration"
    
        @{u}@{b}Screen configuration@{uu}@{ub}

    (R) = needs reqtools.library

    @{b}1. Select main screen's size and mode @{ub}(R)@{b}
    2. Select text viewer screen's size and mode @{ub}(R)@{b}
    3. Select text font @{ub}(R)@{b}
    4. Select list font@{ub} (non-proportional) (R)@{b}
    5. Select requester font @{ub}(R)@{b}
    6. Select text viewer font @{ub}(non-proportional) (R)@{b}
    7. Select small font @{ub}(This font is used if requester doesn't fit
       on screen with requester font) (R)@{b}
    8. Layout @{ub}(see below)@{b}
    9. Palette @{ub}(see below)@{ub}

    @{b}Window@{ub}        if yes, FileMaster's main window can be dragged,
            depth arranged and re-sized.
    @{b}Screen@{ub}        Public screen=FileMaster opens its screen as a
            public screen called 'FM'
            On public screen=FileMaster opens its window on
            public screen written on string gadget
            (defaults to 'Workbench')
            Custom screen=FileMaster opens its screen as a
            custom screen
    @{b}Vertical and horizontal scrolling@{ub}
            Selects smooth or jump scroll for list windows.


    @{u}@{b}Layout@{uu}@{ub}

    This is used to change the number of directory windows on screen
    Unfortunately I don't know how to explain this easily..
    Try it out yourself...

    @{u}@{b}Palette@{uu}@{ub}

    @{u}@{b}name:        affects:@{uu}@{ub}
    @{b}directory@{ub}     directories, devices, volumes and assigns
    @{b}file@{ub}        files and unselectable lines on devicelist
    @{b}text@{ub}        all texts outside of directory windows
    @{b}highlight@{ub}    selected items background
    @{b}back@{ub}        text background
    @{b}backfill@{ub}    requesters' background
    @{b}main backfill@{ub}    FileMaster window's background
    @{b}source list@{ub}    source's color (background of free/used-text)
    @{b}dest list@{ub}    destination's color (background of free/used-text)
    @{b}scroller@{ub}    scroll bars
    @{b}path@{ub}        path string gadgets' background

    @{b}Edit palette@{ub}    palette editor (R)

    @{u}@{b}ShowTrumb Size@{uu}@{ub} (3.2B1)  Here can set the Trumpnail size in Pixel.

    @{u}@{b}Progressbar@{uu}@{ub}

     You can set different types for Progressbar.


     None - Switch the Progressbar off     
 
     Simple - use only one color, that you can coose via the palette Gadget
     
     Course - use a color course. The (base)color of it can selected
              via the slider. Require that FM runs on a Screen with more then 8 Bit(CGX, P96).
          Course is less! CPU intensive and should used if CGX/P96 is available.    
     
    
@ENDNODE
@NODE CON_User "FileMaster 3.1: Build-in / User commands"

    @{u}@{b}Commands@{uu}@{ub}

    Configuration for commands
    (see @{b}@{" build-in commands " link BuildinCmds}@{ub} section for details)
    Next page toggles between build-in and user commands

    @{u}User Commands:@{uu}

    F1-F10 starts user commands 1-10 and Shift+F1-F10 user commands 11-20

    @{b}Window@{ub}        open a shell window?
    @{b}CD@{ub}        CD to destination, source or don't change
    @{b}Rescan@{ub}        reread source, destination or both
            after command is executed
    @{b}Start screen@{ub}    pop Workbench or FileMaster to front
            before executing command
    @{b}End screen@{ub}    pop Workbench or FileMaster to front
            after command is executed
    @{b}Label@{ub}        gadget's label
    @{b}Pattern@{ub}        *.(lha|lzh) for lha archives etc...
            user command is executed if user doubleclicks
            file with matching pattern
    @{b}Signature@{ub}    offset,$hexadecimal bytes/"string",offset...
            if doubleclicked file has these bytes starting from
            offset byte then this file will be executed
            check out default user commands for examples!
    @{b}Command@{ub}        executable command with parameters
    @{b}Stack@{ub}        size of stack

    @{u}parameters:@{uu}

        @{b}{d}@{ub}        Destination directory name
        @{b}{f}@{ub}        First selected entry (with path)
        @{b}{F}@{ub}        All selected entries (with paths)
        @{b}{o}@{ub}        First selected entry (name only)
        @{b}{O}@{ub}        All selected entries (names only)
        @{b}{r,text}@{ub}    String requester
                text=string gadget's label
        @{b}{s}@{ub}        Source directory name

@ENDNODE
@NODE CON_General "FileMaster 3.1: General Configuration"

    @{u}@{b}General@{uu}@{ub}

    @{b}Multitasking@{ub}        turns FM's internal multitasking on and off
                when this is on, you can swap directory
                buffers and/or run many commands at the
                same time.
    @{b}Main priority@{ub}        FM main process' priority
    @{b}Low/Med/High priority@{ub}    priority levels for commands
    @{b}File buffer size@{ub}    size of buffer for disk operations
    @{b}Doubleclick time@{ub}    doubleclick time in hundreds of seconds
    @{b}Right mouse button@{ub}    doubleclick/Parent

@ENDNODE
